SIMPLE: diviner
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Diviner
<hw>Di*vin"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
professes divination; one who pretends to predict events, or to reveal
occult things, by supernatural means.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>diviners</qex> have seen a lie, and have told false
dreams; they comfort in vain.</q> <rj><qau>Zech. x. 2.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A conjecture; a guesser; one who makes out occult
things.</def> <rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Divineress</ent>⟦br⟧
